<codeline lineno="8"><highlight class="comment"><sp/>*<sp/>The<sp/>`ChildrenKinematics`<sp/>class,<sp/>implemented<sp/>in<sp/>Cython,<sp/>is<sp/>a<sp/>specialized<sp/>selection<sp/>template<sp/>within<sp/>the<sp/>AnalysisG<sp/>framework,<sp/>designed<sp/>for<sp/>detailed<sp/>analysis<sp/>of<sp/>the<sp/>kinematic<sp/>properties<sp/>of<sp/>particles<sp/>originating<sp/>from<sp/>top<sp/>quark<sp/>decays<sp/>in<sp/>Monte<sp/>Carlo<sp/>16<sp/>(MC16)<sp/>events.<sp/>It<sp/>extends<sp/>the<sp/>generic<sp/>`SelectionTemplate`<sp/>class,<sp/>providing<sp/>tailored<sp/>functionalities<sp/>for<sp/>handling<sp/>various<sp/>kinematic<sp/>observables,<sp/>particle<sp/>identification<sp/>(PDG<sp/>ID),<sp/>and<sp/>decay<sp/>modes.<sp/>This<sp/>class<sp/>facilitates<sp/>a<sp/>high-performance<sp/>extraction<sp/>and<sp/>organization<sp/>of<sp/>children<sp/>kinematics<sp/>data<sp/>for<sp/>further<sp/>physics<sp/>analysis.</highlight></codeline>
